On Friday 19 September 2003 05:48, Eugen Leitl wrote:
> The publishers knows the cryptographic hash of the document, and can
> submit it to full-text indexing search services. Each P2P node should
> come with a search engine, which uses part of the store space to keep
> an index.

The httpsy scheme is not intended for P2P distribution of
immutable content. Look at something like Mnet for that. The
httpsy scheme is intended for hosting of active computing agents,
like say an e-gold account. These two problems are very different
and have different solutions.

Tyler

